The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and the hearth. Plaster the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Build a custom closet.
We always start with a quick sketch in pencil...
The messy step is finished.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried up :(
Ready for plastering next week
Pleased with the little niche on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a lovely little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney sweep installed the cap and the baffle. This should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll install the floor tomorrow !
The cork underlayment is laid, and I improvised a wood shavings extractor using a toilet paper roll as an accessory for the vacuum 😂
Part of the planks are sorted and ready to install. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress was slow today due to very delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the corridor (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on the knees! Cherry on top: the unpalatable instructions for assembling the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
Left to do: the corridor floor and all the baseboards. The decorator is coming in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's all about plaster chic without any fuss
Evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw or chisel where we want the floor to be perfectly fitted.
The cork underlayment for the corridor is also installed
We finished the corridor floor yesterday! Then off at 5 a.m. this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then a siesta and the final stretch for the corridor; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing once the glue has dried.
